title: Jumble Jamboree/Spy Crocs
description: Papa prepares to throw a celebration. Apple takes over when he needs help, determined to make the festival "Papa Perfect." Josh and Jamie wonder where Mama goes without them. They see her with an alligator and think she is croc-napped by an alien!

title: Proper Game/My Friend Biba/Vacuumasaurus
description: Gus insists Lu play dinosaurs properly, Lu gets jealous of Biba's friendship with other bugs, and Lu helps Gus overcome his discomfort.

title: Under the Hood
description: Mordecai and Rigby need to get rid of graffiti in the park.

title: Musical Stool/Doodle Day/Keeping Cool
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures finding solutions that care for all, appreciating their art, and learning ways to keep cool.

title: The Sacred
description: Iyanu, Biyi, Toye and Ekun reach The Source Mountain and meet the Guardians. Iyanu must pass the three Trials to prove she's the Chosen. Meanwhile, Chancellor Nuro, possessed by the Fallen One, tracks them across the Rinku Plains to stop her.

title: Za
description: Pizza's Diner needs a makeover. Apple and Onion better get this right or Pizza is ruined.

title: Falafel's in Jail
description: Falafel's in trouble with the law despite pleading his innocence. Apple and Onion vow to break him out.

title: Champion
description: Stuck with a problematic pet, Apple and Onion need to somehow find a way to get their lives back.

title: For Queen and Country
description: Onion has an unexpected and impossible new love interest. Off to England then.

title: Bubble Trouble/Baby Barnaby/ Lu's Decision
description: Lu and Barnaby play with bubbles, Barnaby plays baby, and Lu has fun in the pool.

title: Things That Go Tweet In The Woods
description: During a camping trip, Sweetie admits she's afraid of something in the woods and after a round of scary stories, everyone finds out what's out there.

title: The Source Part II
description: Iyanu reaches The Source and faces a devastating choice about her destiny. As Elu teeters on the brink of destruction from the Corrupt, Iyanu's allies fight a final battle against Chancellor Nuro and the Fallen One.

title: Dad's Present/Sunday Football/Paddling Problem
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures making a present for Dad, playing football, and trying to fix their paddling pool.

title: The Eyes
description: One night, an exhausted Finn and Jake are creeped out by an odd-looking horse that mysteriously appears outside the treehouse and keeps them awake. They try everything they can think of to get rid of the freaky horse, but nothing seems to work.

title: Happy to Help/ A Jolly Day/ Broken Pot
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures in the garden, playing with Jolly the dog, and repurposing a broken pot.

title: Cousin's Day
description: It's Cousin's Day- another holiday the corporations made up to make more money and Apple and Onion are going to capitalise on it.

title: Spin, Spin, Spin/ Digging Quest/ Happily Never Ending
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures with a pinwheel, a mystery map, and reading a book.

title: Rocky Day/ Leaf Boats /Bike Ride
description: The bugs decorate rocks, collect leaves, and Lu gets a balance bike.

title: Walking on the Ceiling
description: Apple's curiosity of what it would be like to walk upside down like a spider should be ignored and given no further thought. It is not.

title: Sneakerheads
description: Apple & Onion need a Last Will and Testament if they are to protect their belongings from the state.

title: Hero Hotline
description: When Cyborg and Starfire need appliance repair help, they call the Hero Hotline, a unique trio of superheroes.

title: Block Party
description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

title: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers/Firehouse Frolics
description: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers: The Baby Looney Tunes explore a world of botanic wonder as they search for just the right spot to plant a young lemon tree./Firehouse Frolics: The Baby Looney Tunes tour the local fire station, learning fire prevention tips from friendly Fireman Frank. Later, Baby Daffy, the most reluctant and uninterested participant, displays the most fire-fighting knowledge when he is suddenly tested by a real-life emergency at Granny's house.

title: The Prince and the Yucky Duckling
description: A Hooded Stranger from Prince Ivandoe's past seeks revenge by attempting to ruin Ivandoe's perfect princely appearance. Bert repeatedly foils his attempts, so the Hooded Stranger kidnaps Bert and whisks him off to his lair. Time for Prince Ivandoe to rescue Bert and discover just what he did to anger the Hooded Stranger in the first place!
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: The Ape Outdoors/Best Beast
description: Papa takes Apple camping to reduce her screen time. But when they're lost and hungry, Apple's video game skills save the day. Stellar learns that Gazelle Day and Tiger Day are on the same day, so she desperately tries to celebrate both days at once.

title: Pancake's Bus Tour
description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

title: Party Popper
description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

title: The Secret Life of Stripes/Dads of Thunder
description: Apple gets jealous when her pet Stripes plays with her friends while she's gone -- until she realizes how he's helping others. Mama is Josh's hero, but Stellar's Dad becomes his new hero after fixing his soapbox car -- can Josh have TWO heroes?

title: Corner Shop/ Reach for the Sky/ Boat Trip
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures shopping, painting, and preparing for a boat trip.

title: Patty's Law
description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

title: Tales from the Omnitrix
description: Team Tennyson trade campfire stories in an anthology-style series that pits Ben against his archrival, Kevin 11, and teaches our hero the power of imagination.

title: Cruisin
description: Mordecai and Rigby make a bet with Margaret and Eileen that they can get a girl's phone number by cruising.

title: Falafel's Glory
description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

title: Time to Bake/ Dino Story/ Bubble Trouble
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures baking a pie, telling stories, and playing with bubbles.

title: Wall Painting/ Thanking Fountain/ Stormy Sunday
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures painting a wall, going to the Thanking Fountain, and finding fun in a thunderstorm.

title: Uncle Lorcan/Baby Trouble/ Bright Beetle Lu
description: Uncle Lorcan plays with Lu and Biba, Lola chomps on Tara's tail, and Lu struggles with her new costume.

title: The Eater
description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

title: Ruler's Rule
description: Robin teaches the Titans how to use a ruler.

title: Traffic Lights/Cauliflower Picnic/Building Bots
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures inventing a new game, trying new things, and sharing their creativity.

title: Meet the Rocks/ A Fruity Mix Up/ Kitty Adventure
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures with Rocky, a family recipe, and Marzipants the cat.

title: Falafel's Passion
description: Apple and Onion try to help Falafel find his passion but it looks like things might take a humiliating turn.

title: Tips
description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

title: The Box/Spotty Rocket/Goodbye Rainboots
description: Lu shares a box with Barnaby, decorates a rocket with Gus, and says goodbye to her favorite rain boots.

title: Copy! Copy!/Light Home/Mystery Sheet
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures copying each other, visiting the Lighthouse, and guessing what Granny's sheet is for.

title: These Little Piggies Went to Market/Now Museum, Now You Don't
description: These Little Piggies Went to Market: Their first trip to a big grocery store fascinates the Baby Looney Tunes. After warning the others to stick to Granny's shopping list, Baby Bugs succumbs to buying a favorite treat then feels guilty./Now Museum, Now You Don't: Their very first trip to an art museum unleashes creative energy, turning the Baby Looney Tunes into enthused culture connoisseurs and budding artists. Baby Bugs recreates the museum experience back at Granny's house, finding abundant art history in everyday objects to the others' sheer delight.

title: Brain Food
description: BB avoids being "the dumb one" by making the rest of the Titans dumber, which leaves only Silkie to save the day.

title: Mom-and-Daughter Day Disaster/Croc's Got Talent
description: On Mommy-Daughter Day, Stellar and her mom have different ideas about how to spend the day: princesses or dinosaurs! For the talent show, Stellar and Piper practice magic, Apple and Stripes dance, but Josh and Jamie struggle to find a double act.

title: Pat on the Head
description: Apple and Onion are to cook for a very important guest but Onion is not quite feeling himself.

title: Crack the Whip
description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!

title: Petri
description: Apple and Onion must get back to their apartment to put the lid on their petri dish.

title: All Work and No Play
description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

title: Grow Lines/Packing for France/Elodie's Graduation
description: The bugs get measured, Lu packs for a trip, and celebrate Elodie's graduation.

title: Jerk Chicken
description: In pursuit of the American Dream, Apple and Onion start their own business. However, a rather troublesome customer stands in their way.

title: 4 on 1
description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

title: Treasure Hunt/Toy Hospital/Silly Soup
description: The bugs search for rocks, bring home toys to school, and help Lu make her silly soup.

title: Follow Your Dreams
description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

title: In and Out
description: Robin goes undercover to destroy the Hive...right after he enjoys some of their perks.

title: Rotten Apple
description: Onion's Dad becomes convinced that Apple is a bad influence on his son.

title: A Bug's Strife/Iddy Biddy Road Trippy
description: Jungle bugs appear while Stellar and Dad dig their vegetable garden. Stellar protests to protect the bugs from insect spray! When friends delay the trip to an Iddy Biddy concert, Apple fears she'll miss seeing her favorite squiddy celebrity.

title: Whisk3ers/The Grumble Games
description: The kids each get a new bunny tech toy called Whisk3rs. The toys are so much fun, the kids forget about their own families! The kids insist they don't whine, but the parents disagree! To prove it, they compete to last all day without complaining.

title: The Inbetween
description: Apple and Onion have promised they will be there for Falafel's birthday party. However, they find themselves in a mysterious place and don't know how to get out.

title: Bend It Like Petunia/He'll Be Zoomin' Round the Mountain (song)/Cock-A-Doodle-Doo-It!
description: Bend It Like Petunia: The Baby Looney Tunes learn all about soccer from Floyd, who surprisingly is an enthused soccer expert. At first awkward, Baby Petunia works the hardest and displays the best sportsmanlike attitude, eventually becoming the very finest all-around soccer player of all the Baby Looney Tunes./Cock-A-Doodle Doo It!: On their first farm visit, the Baby Looney Tunes meet a young, dispirited rooster named Baby Foghorn Leghorn. They work together to build his self-confidence, unleashing powers of persuasion and elocution that even Foghorn never knew he had.

title: The Understanding
description: Gumball and Darwin find themselves in serious trouble when they agree to everything the new kid in school says. The truth is they can't understand a word that he says. Peter Pepperoni has been home schooled and developed a very odd way of speaking. Due to a series of misunderstandings Gumball and Darwin end up on the run from the law.

title: Appleoni
description: The wrong person is getting credit for a new dance craze.

title: The Prince and the Legendary Rabbit Hood
description: Mistaking Prince Ivandoe for a lowly peasant, Rabbit Hood bestows upon him precious jewelry - that she has stolen from a Prince. Prince Svan to be precise! Who is none too pleased to discover his precious items in Ivandoe's possession! Ivandoe and Bert evade capture and set off on a quest to find Rabbit Hood. They must persuade her to return Svan's treasures, thereby clearing Ivandoe's princely name.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Laundry Life/Everything About Everywhere/Guess What?!
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures helping with the laundry, looking for Super Sam, and guessing what they pretend to be.

title: Sunday Helpers/Skip, Skip, Skipping/A Place to Paint
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures helping their family, learning to skip, and painting a birthday cake.

title: Ask Not What Bunnies Can Do for You
description: It's student council elections at Acme Loo! Babs and Buster both run for President, and they enlist Sweetie and Hamton as their respective campaign managers. That just leaves Plucky…who of course decides that he'd make the best President!

title: Little Buddies
description: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

title: Pulling Your Weight
description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

title: The Fly
description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

title: Captain McPrincess/Young Grandad
description: Apple role-plays as Captain McPrincess. Daddy offers help, but Apple insists she doesn't need it ... until her arch enemy swings in. Josh and Jamie recreate a special day for Grandad Crocker, hoping to find the treasure he buried long ago.

title: Yelloween/Lunch Ahoy
description: It's Yelloween! Stellar tries to protect Piper from being scared -- but a mysterious pineapple-gobbling goblin suddenly appears! When Stellar brings her own lunch to Pirate Diner and it goes missing, the kids become pirates to find the lost "treasure."

title: Apple's in Trouble
description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

title: Rumble Brothers/The Blame Game
description: Twins Josh and Jamie are usually together, but they seek their own space after a big argument ... until a storm breaks out! Stellar proves her innocence by playing detectives with Josh ... and pinning the blame on Piper.

title: Googs
description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

title: River of Gold
description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

title: The Prince and the Birthday Bluesies
description: When Prince Ivandoe gets a case of the "Birthday Bluesies", Bert is determined to throw him a Stag Kingdom party with all of his favorite treats. Meanwhile an increasingly "sophisticated" Ivandoe becomes curious to discover the grown-up world.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: The Other Side
description: Craig, Kelsey and JP must journey past the Overpass into uncharted territory, the Other Side of the Creek.

title: Windy Day/ Hand Me Downs/ Me and My Shadow
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures with paper boats, sharing hand me downs, and learning there are more ways than one to play.

title: Got to Go/Bye-Bye Octi/Family Photo
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures getting ready for a party, making friends with an octopus, and taking pictures around the patio.

title: White Elephant
description: The Titans are forced to play a game of White Elephant to save their Christmas presents.

title: Scary Tara/Home School Day/New Library Book
description: Lu meets big Tara, helps Dad with work, and searches the library for a new book.

title: Long Long Line/The Chalk/Elodie Wants to Decide
description: Biba waits in line, the bugs get some new chalk, and Lu meets Elodie's cousin.

title: Win It or Bin It
description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

title: Keep It Fresh
description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

title: The Fast and The Furriest/A Tale of Two Forts
description: Apple realizes it's her own fault that she's always late to school! With Papa, they race the clock to get to school on time. Apple and Josh's creative differences split them up to build two forts -- a princess castle and a rocket ship.

title: Babies on the Block/Beach Bath/The Biggest Joy
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures playing with their baby friends, building a bath at the beach, and remembering joyful family moments.

title: Positive Attitude Theory
description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

title: I Can Catch/That's My Favourite/Tidy Up
description: Lu learns to accept help, Declan learns to share a favorite thing, and Biba learns that accidents happen.

title: The Exiles
description: Fleeing the evil Chancellor Nuro, Iyanu meets the Corrupt Divine Beast Ekun and a mysterious boy named Biyi. As she uncovers her extraordinary powers, she also explores hidden treasures beyond the Walls of Elu.

title: Too Far
description: When Baby Bop's playful teasing starts bothering Mel, Barney arranges a trip to the Castleverse where their adventure motivates Mel to finally speak up for herself.

title: Beach Packing/Swim Class/Wakey Wakey
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures getting ready for the beach, learning to swim, and trying to stay awake for the fireworks.

title: Musical Sundays/Choices Choices/Balloon Rocket
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures playing music, having lunch at the beach, and making a balloon experiment.

title: Finders Not Keepers
description: When Mel discovers the sunglasses she found belong to Grady, she still wants to keep them. Barney creates a high-seas adventure, where Mel realizes she's acting like a pirate taking what doesn't belong to her and returns the glasses.

title: The Dolly Vanishes/Vive Le Pew, Le Skunk (song)/Duck's Reflucks
description: The Dolly Vanishes: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view./Duck's Reflucks: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

title: Ice to Beat You
description: A chilling challenge inside an iceberg leads to the coldest elimination of the season.

title: The Chosen
description: When a teenage orphan girl, Iyanu, unknowingly triggers her Divine Powers, she escapes Elu, the last standing city in the known world, and embarks on a remarkable journey to discover the truth about the evil lurking in the realm of Yorubaland.

title: I, Butler
description: The Bears use a robot bear to help around the house. But things get tricky when they lose control of the robot.

title: Power Flower/Baby Horsefly/Margo Mayfly
description: Declan makes the rules, visits the horsefly stables, and the bugs welcome a visitor.

title: When's My Turn?/A Twig's Tale/Play With Me!
description: The bugs learn to take turns, Lu meets Barnaby's favorite twig, and Lu gets distracted by Biba's baby brother!

title: Truffle Season
description: It's Truffle Season, Apple and Onion are Truffle Hunters and they will stop at nothing to taste a truffle.

title: My Frabulous Family/Paw Pixie
description: When Apple feels like the loneliest only child, she searches for the perfect sibling amongst her friends. When Stellar loses her first claw and worries it won't grow back, Apple invents a "Paw Pixie" to comfort her.

title: I Got a New Aptitude
description: Buster, Plucky, and Hamton take an aptiTOON test that yields some surprising career prospects. Meanwhile, Babs and Sweetie's relaxing dorm-cation is interrupted by a mysterious smell, and they can't rest until they find the source.

title: Opposites
description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

title: Good Job
description: Falafel is starting to feel very underappreciated as the building's handyman. What's the point in all this back breaking work if not a single person will ever tell him, "Good Job"?

title: Paperboyz
description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

title: Drone Shoes
description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

title: One Hit Wonder
description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

title: Barney's Birthday
description: The kids are making a quilt for Barney's birthday featuring their favorite things to do with Barney. David has a hard time choosing just one thing, so Baby Bop and Billy help him decide just in time for the party.

title: Lil Noodle
description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!/Backstage Bugs
description: Lights, Camera, Tweety!: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!/Backstage Bugs: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

title: Birds
description: Robin tries to destroy some pesky mocking birds but they come back bigger, stronger, and ready to mock.

title: The Transformation
description: Penny's family is unhappy that she's decided to come out of her shell literally. And Penny wants her family to come out of their shells...also literally. They are at an impasse so who do they turn to in their time of trouble? Gumball of course! Needless to say he is way outside of his comfort zone.

title: A New Life
description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

title: Birth Day Tales/Meer-kitties
description: As everyone waits for the birth of Stripes' meerkat babies, the kids recount stories of their own first birthdays. When Apple's Dads insist on giving Stripes' meerkat pups to other homes, Apple hides them in her room.

title: The Music Store Thief
description: Instruments have been going missing from Apple and Onion's favourite music store and Chicken Nugget (who's in charge of security) doesn't want them hanging around and getting in the way.

title: Apple's Focus
description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

title: Election Day
description: Apple and Onion realize that the Mayor of their city is corrupt and they vow to put an end to that.

title: Fort Williams
description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

title: Blood Under the Skin
description: Finn goes on an embarrassing quest to get armor to fit in with some really cool knights.

title: A Matter of Pride
description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

title: The Perfect Team
description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

title: Bro, Where's the Batmobile?
description: After a fun night out, Birdarang and Batarang must retrace their steps to find the Batmobile.

title: Broccoli
description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

title: Falafel's Car Keys
description: Apple & Onion are deemed responsible enough to borrow Falafel's car for their first road trip together. Nothing will go wrong, and they're going to make sure of that… by getting some practice in.

title: Oversimulated Much
description: Clover feels that Zerlina doesn't take her seriously as a spy and is determined to prove herself at WOOHP Training Day. But when the simulations go wrong and agents blank out, the Spies realize a secret mastermind is causing the chaos.

title: Log Cabin Fever/A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
description: Log Cabin Fever: Granny takes the Baby Looney Tunes back to a simpler lifestyle during a rustic weekend spent in an 1800's log cabin, where they learn to enjoy life minus all modern conveniences. Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy get in trouble for smuggling their palm-sized computer game along, and they face Granny's consequences./A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

title: The Spinoffs
description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

title: Let Them Eat Quack
description: Plucky is named ruler of a kingdom, and the toons visit his castle as he ascends the throne. Before long, Plucky exerts power over his friends, Sweetie tries to overthrow the monarchy, and Hamton lives out his fantasy of the landed gentry.

title: Run, Mama, Run!/Rainbow Rhino BURP Tomato
description: Apple and Stellar help Mama Crocker attend both Josh's diving and Jamie's ballet performance. Apple and her friends form a pop band to cheer up grumpy Papa. But will their song warm his heart, or hurt his ears?

title: Lil' Squid
description: The Baby Bears build a submarine and explore the depths of an aquarium so they can bring a lost squid to its family.

title: Gotcha/Sing Along/Big Laugh
description: The bugs play hide and seek, sing a song, and laugh together.

title: Christmas Spirit
description: Apple & Onion know exactly what gifts they want this Christmas but all their money has been squandered. Luckily they find a suitably festive way to make back that money.

title: Daddy Date Night/Croc Swap
description: Apple is anxious about her Dads leaving her with a babysitter on their date night. But she has a solution: She'll join them! Annoyed that they're treated the same on their birthday, Josh and Jamie swap places to see if their friends notice.

title: World Cup
description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

title: Burger's Trampoline
description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

title: Beta
description: Steven and Amethyst visit some friends in the country but Amethyst isn't being herself.

title: You Poor Saps
description: Tensions run high in this week's challenge when the Campers find themselves in a sticky situation.

title: Apple's in Charge
description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

title: The Monsters in Your Head
description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

title: Birds of a Feather
description: When Vivie longs to be just like a beautiful bird in the park, Barney uses games and imaginative play to help her discover ways to enjoy a similar experience of looking, singing, and even flying like a bird!

title: The Big Pop/A Very Bananas Wedding
description: Apple worries that her Dads will live happily ever after without her, so she plots to stop the marriage proposal! Apple offers to plan Papa and Daddy's big day, but the surprise fairytale wedding turns into a fairytale fail!

title: Blast Off Bugs/Baby Brouhaha
description: Blastoff Bugs: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit./Baby Brouhaha: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

title: Fortune Cookie
description: Rigby swaps fortune cookie fortunes with Benson.

title: The Pink Painter Strikes Again
description: They're baaaaack! All 16 Campers from Season One return for more spills, thrills and dramaaaaa! And a very special guest arrives on the island to really mess things up. Hope everyone packed an extra pair of pants!

title: Jungle Jet/Vacation Island
description: The families board a plane for vacation. When Apple's tablet breaks, the kids try to entertain themselves on the long flight. On Vacation Island, the parents want to relax, but the kids rope them into a contest to see who can win the vacation!

title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

title: Squash Me if You Can
description: Sweetie competes in a cat vs. bird competition but faces pressure to win at all costs. Hamton and Babs go into soccer mom-mode cheering her on, while Plucky, at the Loo Bru, takes over Dizzy's shift to prove he's more selfless than Buster.

title: Gut Grinder
description: Finn and Jake chase a mysterious villain who's been stealing gold from helpless villages.

title: The Source Part I
description: As Cursed animals besiege Elu, Iyanu searches for The Source. Meanwhile, Biyi, Toye, Olori and Kanfo launch a counterattack against Chancellor Nuro and his forces, who are trying to prevent Iyanu from lifting the Curse on Yorubaland.

title: Kelsey the Elder
description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

title: Dragonhead
description: In desperate need of a shower due, Apple and Onion resort to desperate measures.

title: Eyesore a Sunset
description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

title: Fun Proof
description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

title: Bear Squad
description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

title: Carried Away/ Tram Trip/ The Package
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures playing as ants, taking the tram to the beach, and learning that the thought counts.

title: Betty the Bookworm/ Costume Day/Barnaby's Choice
description: Gus finds his voice, the bugs wear costumes to school, and Barnaby can't choose between Lu and Biba's games.

title: Steven vs. Amethyst
description: Steven and Amethyst get competitive while training with Pearl.

title: Time Twisters/Escape From Planet Play-Day
description: Apple wishes to be older and deletes a childish video on Daddy's phone. Will going back in time make it all right? Stellar is fed up with Piper's toddler behavior, but when she gets trapped with her friends, Piper's toddler ways save day!

title: Nothing Can Stop Us
description: Hot Dog has the audition of his life but he is missing something crucial. Apple and Onion are tasked with bringing it to him and they are adamant that nothing will stand in their way.

title: Not Funny
description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

title: Lowlifes
description: Apple & Onion cannot allow themselves to be viewed by society- and more importantly by smug old Chicken Nugget-as lowlifes.

title: A Bully for Bugs/The Wheel Deal
description: A Bully for Bugs: With Floyd's adult assistance, Baby Bugs and the Baby Looney Tunes learn an effective way to deal with a bully. /The Wheel Deal: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

title: Are We There Yet/Save Our Cinnamon
description: Are We There, Yet?: During a long road trip, Floyd, obsessed with taking the Baby Looney Tunes to visit the distant, annual Acme Garlic Festival, endures countless variants of the universal kid question, are we there, yet? Despite Floyd's garlic agenda, fate has other plans./Save Our Cinnamon: Granny's sister's beloved bakery, Cakery Bakery Dock, home of her wonderful trademark cinnamon rolls, is being put out of business so her landlord can tear down the bakery to build a parking lot. This galvanizes the Baby Looney Tunes to work together to bake one giant cinnamon roll as a tourist attraction to save the bakery, a project that ends up involving the whole town.

title: A Turtle Named Mrytle/Oh My Darling Coyote (song)/There's Nothing Like a Good Book
description: A Turtle Named Myrtle: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so that she may take Myrtyle home for herself./There's Nothing Like a Good Book: A nagging question regarding the composition of the moon brings the Baby Looney Tunes to experience their very first visit to the library.

title: Camp Coconuts/Josh the Butterfly
description: The kids go to pirate camp for an overnight adventure. When Josh misses Mama, Jamie helps him get over his homesickness. The kids dress up for the Jungle Towers Bug Parade! Josh wants to be a butterfly but wonders if it's tough enough.

title: Lambporcini
description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

title: Sour Candy Trials
description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

title: Cricket Chorus/A Sunday Puzzle/Sleep Over
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures searching for a cricket, making a puzzle, and trying to fall asleep.

title: Panamanian Night Monkey
description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

title: Bottle Catch
description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

title: It Came From the Nightosphere
description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

title: Penguin Please/Swing Me/The Long Goodbye
description: Lu opens a shop, goes on the swings, and plays with her favorite uncle who's come to visit.

title: Papa The Daddy/Bubble Brother
description: Apple misses her fun Daddy, so her serious Papa lets loose. When things go bananas, she learns she wants silly and sensible. Jamie hurts his tail, and Josh vows to nurse him back to health but takes it too far -- Jamie ends up in a bubble!

title: Apple's Short
description: Apple wants to experience love.

title: Apple's Formula
description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

title: Battle of the Dads/Yeah, Yeah, Yeah Day!
description: The three dads audition to be Josh and Jamie's Dad for a day. Apple's Dads realize they've been saying "No" to her a lot, so they give her a Yeah-Yeah-Yeah Day. But will she spend it wisely?

title: Hole In Roof
description: Suddenly the hole in the roof is no longer a laughing matter but one of a life or death.

title: Open House Cookies
description: Jerk Chicken is selling his house and Apple and Onion have been showing a lot of interest which definitely has nothing to do with the delicious cookies out on offer.

title: Baby Boi TP
description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

title: Face Your Fears
description: Apple and Onion must face their fears if they are to save French Fry from their bad advice.

title: Find the Blueberries/Green-Eyed Birthday Monster/ But Why?
description: Lu and Biba play a hiding game, Biba has a birthday party, and Dots the Dogfly comes to visit.

title: Whale Spotting
description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

title: Swim Class/Squeak Jumps/Boat Trip
description: Lu goes to swim class, jumps on a squeaky toy, and goes on a boat trip.

title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?/Flu the Coop
description: Oh, Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure./Flu the Coop: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

title: The Ad
description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

title: Choosin' For a Bruisin'
description: Our campers get tested on how well they know each other. Correct answers could win them immunity, but incorrect answers drop them into a pool of hungry wolverines.

title: Weekend at Benson's
description: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock out Benson and try to cover it up.

title: Gyranoid of the Future
description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

title: Slobbery
description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

title: The Prince and the Chosen One
description: When Bert unknowingly pulls a sword from a stone, he is suddenly appointed the leader of the Heroic Council of Heroes. And Prince Ivandoe is appointed…Bert's squire! Ivandoe struggles with this role reversal and decides to show everyone who the real hero is!
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Falafel's Fun Day
description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

title: What Woolly Mammoth
description: The Spies are sent on a chilly mission to stop a villain who has brought woolly mammoths back to life, but can they bring down the nefarious knitter before the Earth is sent back to the Ice Age? Brrr!

title: Roly Poly Disappearance/Ask Me First/When Bugs Cry
description: Lu cares for a pet, shares some treats, and helps a friend to express themself.

title: Selfish Shellfish
description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

title: Think Positive
description: Pops orders Benson to stop yelling at Mordecai and Rigby.

title: Filthy Rich
description: What does it take to be truly content? Whatever it takes, Apple and Onion are going to achieve it.

title: Bismuth
description: Steven discovers something the Gems thought was lost to the past inside of Lion's mane.

title: Undercover Supervillains
description: The spies go undercover as supervillains, but Alex puts the mission in jeopardy when she enjoys being a baddie a little too much! Will she remember how to be good in time to save the mission?

title: Take Us Out to the Ballgame/Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind
description: Take Us Out to the Ball Game: The Baby Looney Tunes experience their very first big stadium baseball game. Lola's favorite team's star batter gets her undivided attention until Lola's coaching affects the very outcome of the contest./Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind: Tweety feels neglected when no one wants him on their museum scavenger hunt team. Using his innate sleuthing abilities and the help of a friendly museum guard, Tweety proves to be the best scavenger hunter of them all. Once Tweety wins the contest, everyone wants him on their team.

title: Microwave's Dance Club
description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

title: Heatwave
description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

title: Number One Jamie/Bouncing Around
description: When Mama chants "You're Number One" to Josh, Jamie thinks this means he's number two, so he plots to win against Josh. Stellar enjoys her activity classes, but when she learns there are prizes to win, she pressures herself to succeed at all costs.

title: The Dah-Who?
description: Rumours are flying that a strange mythical creature is causing snowboarders to disappear. But that won't stop Clover reconnecting with her old flame Blaine on the slopes...

title: Taking it to the Rim Reaper
description: Things get wet, wild and gross when the Campers play waterslide basketball!

title: Apple & Onion's Booth
description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

title: The Prince and the Nutty Wedding
description: When Prince Ivandoe triumphantly finds the One True Acorn during a rigged royal contest, he also finds himself betrothed to the psychotic Princess Sprinklejoy of the Red Squirrel Kingdom. Whilst narrowly managing to avoid a royal wedding, both Ivandoe & Bert end up in the Pit of Ow instead…which, all things considered, is actually preferable.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Totally Pawsome
description: When Alex brings home a basket of kittens, Clover smells a rat. Turns out she's right as Clover gets catnapped by an evil villain who is determined to infiltrate WOOHP. But as the spies fight back, they realize this villain is not working alone...

title: Mel's Hair/ Watermelon Picking/ Star Light Star Bright
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures brushing each others hair, picking watermelons, and discovering natural wonders around them.

title: The Prince and the Ducky Day
description: For Prince Ivandoe every day feels exactly the same…because it is!!! And he's the only one who can see it. Has it something to do with that mysterious Ducky and the so-called "Ducky Day"? Is Ivandoe stuck in this loop forever or will he once again get to "Quest on!"?
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Squeaky Squid/Mon Ami Celeri/Wiggling & Flapping
description: Lu and Biba get surprise toys, Lu and Elodie think they've broken a toy, and the bugs play in the snow.

title: The Roller Ride/Butterfly Flutterby/Hopscotch
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures roller skating along the promenade, drawing a butterfly, and playing hopscotch with their friends.

title: Cupcake Surprise/A New Pet/Don't Wanna Miss Out
description: The bugs get cupcakes, a class pet, and choose from a selection of fun activities.

title: The Missing Valentine
description: When Barney notices that Vivie forgot to make a valentine for someone special on Valentine's Day, the kids embark on a magical quest to find out who it is. They complete challenges that help Vivie realize she forgot to make one for herself!

title: Loyalty to the King
description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

title: Wrong!/Win, Lose or Daffy
description: Wrong!: On an orchard outing, picking bushels of fresh apples for Granny's home-baked pies, the Baby Looney Tunes encounter Melissa, who is in a mood to tell everyone that her method of apple picking is the only way./Win, Lose or Daffy: A day playing miniature golf is fun for everyone but Baby Daffy, who believes he must beat everyone else at the game. At the end of the day, all but Daffy are having a good time regardless of how they scored.

title: Ferekh
description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

title: Onionless
description: Onion needs to leave town so Apple has to survive the weekend alone while taking care of Onion's beloved plant.
